DESCRIPTION:<a href="https://bots.rba.community/">https://bots.rba.communit
 y/</a><br><br><a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/southwest-boss-of-the-s
 oc-bots-spring-2025-tickets-1246726495509?aff=oddtdtcreator">https://www.ev
 entbrite.com/e/southwest-boss-of-the-soc-bots-spring-2025-tickets-124672649
 5509?aff=oddtdtcreator</a><br><br><br>Southwest States Splunk Event: Boss o
 f the SOC (BOTS)<br><br>Boss of the SOC (BOTS) is a cutting-edge\, team-bas
 ed cybersecurity competition designed to replicate real-world challenges fa
 ced by today’s Security Operations Centers (SOCs). Participants will work i
 n teams to investigate\, detect\, and respond to simulated security inciden
 ts using Splunk’s leading security tools. This dynamic competition fosters 
 critical thinking\, problem-solving\, and analytical skills\, all while pro
 viding a unique learning opportunity.<br><br>Key Objectives:<br><ul><li>Gai
 n hands-on experience with Splunk’s Security Suite and other cybersecurity 
 tools.</li><li>Learn to investigate and respond to cybersecurity incidents 
 in a real-time\, high-pressure environment.</li><li>Develop advanced threat
  detection\, investigation\, and response techniques that are immediately a
 pplicable in SOCs.</li><li>Collaborate in teams to solve complex security c
 hallenges.</li></ul>Who Should Attend:<br><ul><li>Students studying cyberse
 curity\, computer science\, or information technology.</li><li>Cybersecurit
 y professionals looking to sharpen their SOC skills.</li><li>Educators inte
 rested in incorporating hands-on cybersecurity training into their programs
 .</li><li>Anyone passionate about cybersecurity and threat detection.</li><
 /ul>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260404T131017Z
LOCATION:Albuquerque (CNM)\, El Paso (Blue Flame Building)\, Phoenix (GCU)\
 , Las Vegas (UNLV)\, Webex (Virtual)
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:BOTS Splunk-Based CTF
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
