 ><br><br>Southwest States Splunk Event: Boss of the SOC (BOTS)<br><br>Boss 
 of the SOC (BOTS) is a cutting-edge\, team-based cybersecurity competition 
 designed to replicate real-world challenges faced by today’s Security Opera
 tions Centers (SOCs). Participants will work in teams to investigate\, dete
 ct\, and respond to simulated security incidents using Splunk’s leading sec
 urity tools. This dynamic competition fosters critical thinking\, problem-s
 olving\, and analytical skills\, all while providing a unique learning oppo
 rtunity.<br><br>Key Objectives:<br><ul><li>Gain hands-on experience with Sp
 lunk’s Security Suite and other cybersecurity tools.</li><li>Learn to inves
 tigate and respond to cybersecurity incidents in a real-time\, high-pressur
 e environment.</li><li>Develop advanced threat detection\, investigation\, 
 and response techniques that are immediately applicable in SOCs.</li><li>Co
 llaborate in teams to solve complex security challenges.</li></ul>Who Shoul
 d Attend:<br><ul><li>Students studying cybersecurity\, computer science\, o
 r information technology.</li><li>Cybersecurity professionals looking to sh
 arpen their SOC skills.</li><li>Educators interested in incorporating hands
 -on cybersecurity training into their programs.</li><li>Anyone passionate a
 bout cybersecurity and threat detection.</li></ul>
